abstract:
Exploratory one-device dynamic RAM arrays, fabricated with N-channel single-level polycide (WSI
<inf xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">2</inf>
) technology with minimum feature size of 1μm, will be discussed.

A 46ns 32K×8 CMOS RAM fabricated with double metal, double poly 1.2μm P-well technology will be reported. The RAM(59.2mm
<sup xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">2</sup>
) has a 10mW operating power at 1MHz and a 30μW standby power.
